		<td><b>SPC700 Instruction Set Effective Address Regions</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Can someone explain why Figure 3-8-3 on page 188 of book1 of the SNES dev manual has the area under 0x1FFF (i.e. the middle address region column) shaded in for the first 10 addressing modes in the table?  I think that must be an error. The first 10 addressing modes can only access page 0 or page 1, right?<br /><br />I believe the middle address region column is correctly filled in for the mem.bit addressing mode since on the previous page it states that AND1/OR1/EOR1/etc can all access the first 8KB of memory.<br /><br />There are other errors too, like the address region in the third column should be labeled 0xFFFF, not 0x1FFF. And the last addressing mode should be [DP]+Y, not [DP+Y].

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


